SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 54
BY SENATOR WOMACK AND REPRESENTATIVE RISER
CONGRESS. Memorializes Congress to authorize and fully fund the Mississippi River
Basin Fishery Commission Act.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To memorialize the Congress of the United States to support H.R.1514 and R.S.1078 of the
3 119th Congress, entitled the "Mississippi River Basin Fishery Commission Act", and
4 to take such actions as are necessary to ensure the state of Louisiana will join the
5 commission as a voting member upon its passage.
6 WHEREAS, the Mississippi River Basin is the fourth largest watershed in the world
7 and the largest watershed in the nation, draining all or part of thirty-one states and two
8 Canadian provinces, measuring approximately one million two hundred thousand square
9 miles, and covering forty-one percent of the continental United States; and
10 WHEREAS, management of the inland fishery resources of the Mississippi River
11 Basin are shared by thirty-one states, multiple federal agencies, and two Canadian provinces;
12 and
13 WHEREAS, the Mississippi River and its tributaries comprise one of the largest and
14 most valuable eco-systems in the world; and
15 WHEREAS, states, including Louisiana, within the Mississippi River Basin have
16 formed multiple regional interstate partnerships, and one basin-wide partnership, to promote
17 cooperation and communication among the conservation agencies in order to manage the
18 interjurisdictional fishery resources of the basin; and
