1 Mississippi River Basin through the development of a multi-agency program for the joint
2 management and protection of such fishery resources; and
3 WHEREAS, in Louisiana, reproducing populations of invasive carp are expanding
4 in both range and numbers within the major rivers of the state, impacting fisheries
5 production and recreation; apple snails are increasing their range and disrupting food chains;
6 giant salvinia, water hyacinth, and other invasive plants are impacting boating and other
7 recreation and modifying aquatic habitat; and other aquatic invasive species are negatively
8 impacting fisheries production and recreation and the economic output and enjoyment that
9 a healthy fishery brings to the state; and
10 WHEREAS, freshwater fishing provides more than two billion dollars in economic
11 impact to the state of Louisiana.
12 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana hereby
13 memorializes the Congress of the United States to support H.R.1514 and R.S.1078 of the
14 119th Congress, entitled the "Mississippi River Basin Fishery Commission Act", and to take
15 such actions as are necessary to ensure the state of Louisiana will join the commission as a
16 voting member upon its passage.
17 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution shall be transmitted
18 to the secretary of the United States Senate and the clerk of the United States House of
19 Representatives and to each member of the Louisiana delegation to the United States
20 Congress.
